Tim<br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/14/03 6:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Arsenals Prevent India/Pakistan War.</span><hr size=1> But this doesnt factor in the possibility of someone who is not sane and rational, for example, a terrorist, getting a few nukes and blowing them up in major population centers.  MAD doesnt matter to them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tmayes1999>tmayes1999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/14/03 6:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Arsenals Prevent India/Pakistan War.</span><hr size=1> My comments apply only to nuclear armed Nation states.<br>
I was not talking about terrorism by terrorists.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/14/03 6:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Arsenals Prevent India/Pakistan War.</span><hr size=1> the terrorists can get nukes from states.  thats our fear with north korea, more than the fear of a first strike.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuclaeon>Nuclaeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/03 2:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Arsenals Prevent India/Pakistan War.</span><hr size=1> But anyone who supplies those nuclear weapons are doomed should anyone find out.  Giving weapons to someone to use it is just as bad as using themselves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/03 5:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Arsenals Prevent India/Pakistan War.</span><hr size=1> and what if we cant find out who did it?  with so many nuclear nations, its going to be hard to pin anything on a single country <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuclaeon>Nuclaeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/03 11:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Arsenals Prevent India/Pakistan War.</span><hr size=1> There's always the chance someone could get away with it.  However, there are HUGE risks involved.  I'm sure the US and the former Soviet Union had spies in just about every important country, at least ones with nuclear weapons.  There is always the chance Colonel Vladimir Kreznikov of future nuclear state could be bought off to produce evidence or Amir Asgullah, a high ranking member of some Iranian terrorist group could be captured and coerced into talking.  <br>
<br>
This is to say nothing of the potential buyers or the sellers.  However, such a plot would require many, many people.  A nuclear weapon disappearing would definitely create some paper trail in a country's bureaucracy.  Someone is bound to know something who has a price.  Somewhere along the line, there is likely to be some intelligence slip.  Maybe nothing definitive, but enough.<br>
<br>
A nation state would seriously have to consider the consequences.  What if the terrorist group didn't go through with it or got caught?  What if someone on the base where the nuclear weapon was exchanged is really an agent?  How do they know the person buying isn't an enemy agent (or paid off) to capture them in an act of horrific magnitude?  The cost would be assured destruction.  Is it possible to get away with it?  Yes, but would you want to take such a risk where your entire country could be annhilated?  A rational leader would not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2888<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/03 8:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Arsenals Prevent India/Pakistan War.</span><hr size=1> Its not just terrorists either. With all those fingers on buttons its only a matter of time before somebody decides to push one. Some leaders are not rational or sane. Some start out rational and sane but suffer from a loss of their faculties as they age. Some are just callous b*stards. They might see a nuclear war as beneficial to themselves and not be bothered by civilian casualties in their own land. <br>
<br>
So we see two extreme scenarios and each is just as undesirable as the other. <br>
<br>
1) In a World without nukes or very few of them we have no deterrant against international conflict and know from experience we can expect to see huge amounts of bloodshed. <br>
<br>
2) In a World full of nuclear weapons our leaders will try harder to avoid war but eventually it will probably happen anyway.<br>
<br>
We are caught between a rock and a hard place. Still, we don't have any choice about these extremes or any middle ground. Proliferation has been steady since 1944 and nothing on Earth can stop it. I still believe the only answer to the nuclear threat is a bigger stick. Nothing short of inertia weapons under the control of limited numbers of nations can avert the end of human civilisation one day. Providing space can be defended from up and coming nations seizing inertia weapons which seems feasible, we can expect human society to last thousands of years longer. <br>
